&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://emoji.slack-edge.com/T077X51KJEQ/zencoder/2badc69a9292c4c1.png&quot; alt=&quot;:zencoder:&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;emoji&quot; data-stringify-emoji=&quot;:zencoder:&quot;&gt; About Zencoder&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At &lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://Zencoder.ai&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Zencoder.ai&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, we build and orchestrate AI agents that ship real work - code, research, operations, and more. What started as developer tooling is becoming a platform where people and agents collaborate across knowledge work tasks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an experienced engineer to raise the bar on how our organization builds, tests, ships, and operates software - for both human engineers and AI coding agents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is AI harness engineering: the discipline of making the fundamentals (CI/CD, testing, IaC, observability, secure delivery) so solid and well-shaped that agents can work productively inside them. Developer experience and platform engineering are a subset of that work. When the harness is good, humans ship faster and agents stop getting stuck on things that shouldn&#39;t be hard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Security is inseparable from this. AI agents are accelerating both the pace and the shape of vulnerabilities, and secure delivery has to be built into the same stream as everything else - not bolted on.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Product teams own their services, pipelines, and tests. Your job is to raise the ceiling across the org - defining standards, building leverage, and helping teams level up their workflows, tooling, infrastructure, security posture, and necessary changes for AI Agents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on lead role - you&#39;ll set direction and be deep in the code, infra, and pipelines yourself. A lead here is very much a builder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape the platform and infrastructure that everything else runs on — the foundations product teams build on top of&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve the full dev loop: local development, CI/CD, deployment, and production feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive standards around testing, IaC, observability, and secure delivery — and help product teams adopt them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build shared tooling, templates, and golden paths that create real leverage — paved roads teams actually want to use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own secure delivery end-to-end: unify security scanning, secrets management, dependency and supply-chain controls, and pen-testing workflows into the core pipeline so secure-by-default is the path of least resistance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay ahead of the shifting security landscape as AI agents reshape both how vulnerabilities emerge and how they&#39;re exploited&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape repos, tooling, and conventions so coding agents can navigate them efficiently — clear structure, good test signal, fast feedback loops, well-scoped contexts, and docs agents can actually use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure impact against DORA metrics and qualitative signals from engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong software engineering background&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing and building internal platforms - the judgment to know what to abstract, what to expose, and what to leave alone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep experience with CI/CD, automated testing, IaC, and developer tooling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong grasp of modern software security and secure delivery practices (shift-left / SecDevOps)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A product mindset toward internal toolin

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://emoji.slack-edge.com/T077X51KJEQ/zencoder/2badc69a9292c4c1.png&quot; alt=&quot;:zencoder:&quot; width=&quot;20&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;emoji&quot; data-stringify-emoji=&quot;:zencoder:&quot;&gt; About Zencoder&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At &lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://Zencoder.ai&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Zencoder.ai&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, we build and orchestrate AI agents that ship real work - code, research, operations, and more. What started as developer tooling is becoming a platform where people and agents collaborate across knowledge work tasks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role exists&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The way software is built, bought, and adopted is changing faster than any market we’ve seen before.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI is reshaping products, teams, workflows, and entire business functions. As we expand beyond Forgood AI products, how we position, launch, and grow products must evolve as well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Product Marketing and GTM leader who is already operating in that future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a role where we’ll teach you how to use AI. You’ll be joining an AI-first organization where AI is embedded across product development, operations, GTM, and decision-making. We expect you to bring new ideas, frameworks, workflows, and systems that make us better.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want someone who can teach us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Someone who has a strong point of view on how AI changes marketing, messaging, positioning, demand generation, product launches, and category creation and who can turn that thinking into measurable business outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll own&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Messaging &amp;amp; Positioning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own company-wide messaging and positioning across products, audiences, and market segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop differentiated narratives that resonate with executives, practitioners, and business teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex capabilities into simple, compelling customer value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create messaging frameworks that scale across marketing, sales, product, customer success, and partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously refine positioning based on customer feedback, market shifts, and competitive intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Category Creation &amp;amp; Thought Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape how the market thinks about AI-enabled work, collaboration, productivity, and business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build narratives that elevate the conversation beyond features and functionality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with executives to develop industry points of view, keynote messaging, launch narratives, and thought leadership programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish the company as a leader in defining what AI-first organizations look like.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Launches &amp;amp; Growth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead GTM strategy for new products, features, and market expansions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive launch planning, customer storytelling, enablement, analyst relations, and campaign execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build AI-powered systems that accelerate experimentation and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify repeatable growth loops across enterprise, self-serve, partnerships, and community channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive &amp;amp; Market Intelligence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of competitors, market trends, emerging technologies, and customer needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build positioning frameworks and battlecards

